476
00:21:42,050 --> 00:21:45,137
I don't think I'm ready to have sex.

477
00:21:46,346 --> 00:21:48,348
I understand if you want
to break up with me.

478
00:21:48,432 --> 00:21:51,476
I know you don't date girls
who don't put out, so it's cool.

479
00:21:52,102 --> 00:21:54,521
That's not true. I can go slow.

480
00:21:55,522 --> 00:21:58,317
Okay, but what does going slow
mean to you?

481
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:00,819
Like non-stop 69ing?
'Cause I don't want to do that.

482
00:22:00,902 --> 00:22:02,487
What? No.

483
00:22:03,947 --> 00:22:05,407
[sighs]

484
00:22:05,490 --> 00:22:08,577
Look, Devi, I only want to do
what you're comfortable with.

485
00:22:09,369 --> 00:22:12,706
Well, what if what I'm comfortable with

486
00:22:12,789 --> 00:22:15,625
is just going to second base
during scary movies?

487
00:22:16,376 --> 00:22:18,253
-Then I'm cool with that.
-Really?

488
00:22:18,962 --> 00:22:19,963
Yeah.

489
00:22:21,590 --> 00:22:24,092
-You want to watch some TikToks?
-Yeah.

490
00:22:24,176 --> 00:22:25,302
[chuckles]

491
00:22:26,345 --> 00:22:28,013
So we decided to take it slow.

492
00:22:28,096 --> 00:22:30,599
He didn't even get to see the G-string
I made out of my shoelace.

493
00:22:30,682 --> 00:22:32,893
-That's awesome, Devi.
-Good for you.

494
00:22:32,976 --> 00:22:36,355
I mean, we did silkscreen
this "Plowed by Paxton" t-shirt for you,

495
00:22:36,438 --> 00:22:40,233
but I guess I can give it to someone else
who had sex with him. I'm proud of you.

496
00:22:40,317 --> 00:22:42,944
Apricot conditioner, so no flaking.

497
00:22:43,028 --> 00:22:44,738
So, any updates on Trent?

498
00:22:45,572 --> 00:22:49,534
Ugh! No, I've given up on him.
He ghosted me on text.

499
00:22:49,618 --> 00:22:51,787
-I guess I misread the signals.
-[school bell ringing]

500
00:22:51,870 --> 00:22:55,874
Here are your graded pop quizzes
on the Tet Offensive.

501
00:22:55,957 --> 00:23:00,921
And, frankly, what I find offensive
is how ill-prepared so many of you were.

502
00:23:01,004 --> 00:23:04,216
I guess I'll have to go back
to teaching with textbooks

503
00:23:04,299 --> 00:23:06,510
instead of the films of Robert Zemeckis.

504
00:23:07,677 --> 00:23:08,804
I got a flat 100?

505
00:23:08,887 --> 00:23:12,557
But I wrote an extra page
on LBJ's inability to de-escalate the war

506
00:23:12,641 --> 00:23:15,685
and Lady Bird Johnson's lack
of fashion compared to Jackie O's.

507
00:23:15,769 --> 00:23:17,437
I told you, Ben, no more extra credit.

508
00:23:18,355 --> 00:23:20,941
An 82? A freaking 82?

509
00:23:21,024 --> 00:23:24,152
Hey, I also got an 82! Ha! We're the same.

510
00:23:24,236 --> 00:23:27,114
-[scoffs]
-[laughs] Eleanor, up top!

511
00:23:27,614 --> 00:23:31,451
I don't know how this happened.
I've never gotten below an A before.

512
00:23:32,035 --> 00:23:35,497
[McEnroe] In that moment,
Fabiola knew what she had to do.

513
00:23:35,580 --> 00:23:38,041
[emotional music playing]

514
00:23:38,125 --> 00:23:40,043
[Fabiola] Hey, I think we should talk.

515
00:23:40,127 --> 00:23:41,920
[phone dings]

516
00:23:42,003 --> 00:23:44,423
[Eve] Sure,
would 2:30 a.m. your time work?

517
00:23:44,506 --> 00:23:45,382
[sighs]

518
00:23:45,465 --> 00:23:48,135
Ooh, an 84. Suck on that, Trent.

519
00:23:49,052 --> 00:23:50,137
[laughs]

520
00:23:54,599 --> 00:23:56,768
[school bell ringing]

521
00:23:57,352 --> 00:23:58,270
[Trent] Eleanor!

522
00:24:00,105 --> 00:24:02,732
How could you leave me
hanging back there with my high five?

523
00:24:03,442 --> 00:24:05,610
It cuts me deep
that my girl would do that to me.

524
00:24:05,694 --> 00:24:08,238
[Eleanor] Um, I'm sorry. Your girl?

525
00:24:08,321 --> 00:24:09,489
Are we dating?

526
00:24:09,573 --> 00:24:11,450
Because you haven't texted me back
in forever.

527
00:24:11,533 --> 00:24:13,743
Oh, that's because I changed my number.

528
00:24:13,827 --> 00:24:16,830
I found out that 1-800-0FS-GIVEN
became available.

529
00:24:16,913 --> 00:24:18,415
Not that I even give an f.

530
00:24:18,999 --> 00:24:22,377
Okay, so just to clarify,
you have a toll-free cell phone number?

531
00:24:22,461 --> 00:24:24,504
-Yeah.
-And you like me?

532
00:24:24,588 --> 00:24:25,422
Romantically?

533
00:24:25,505 --> 00:24:26,423
Yeah.

534
00:24:27,007 --> 00:24:29,759
[scoffs] Okay, because that wasn't
really clear before.

535
00:24:29,843 --> 00:24:32,512
Oh, well, let me be clear then.

536
00:24:32,596 --> 00:24:35,056
["Prom" by Riah playing]

537
00:24:35,140 --> 00:24:40,562
♪ Don't wanna call
But I'm thinkin' 'bout you ♪

538
00:24:40,645 --> 00:24:43,899
♪ Can't help it if I do ♪

539
00:24:43,982 --> 00:24:46,193
♪ Don't wanna call… ♪

540
00:24:46,276 --> 00:24:47,527
-Wow.
-Sick.

541
00:24:48,236 --> 00:24:49,112
[chuckles]

542
00:24:50,947 --> 00:24:52,449
-[Ben] Hey.
-Hi.

543
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:54,868
Well, how's everything going?

544
00:24:54,951 --> 00:24:56,161
The, you know…

545
00:24:57,162 --> 00:24:58,663
[inaudible conversation]

546
00:24:59,331 --> 00:25:00,999
Things are really good.

547
00:25:02,167 --> 00:25:04,753
Good. Since you're a late bloomer,

548
00:25:04,836 --> 00:25:06,671
I just wanted to offer my advice

549
00:25:06,755 --> 00:25:09,841
as someone with more romantic
and sexual experience.

550
00:25:09,925 --> 00:25:12,219
-Mmm. How kind of you.
-Yeah, no problem.

551
00:25:13,386 --> 00:25:16,598
Great, well, all right.
I'll, uh, see you later, David.

552
00:25:16,681 --> 00:25:17,807
Mmm.

553
00:25:17,891 --> 00:25:19,643
[school bell ringing]

554
00:25:20,727 --> 00:25:22,020
Hey! You three!

555
00:25:22,687 --> 00:25:26,525
I want to let you guys know that Paxton
and I decided to take things slow

556
00:25:26,608 --> 00:25:30,278
because we are in a mature,
committed, respectful relationship

557
00:25:30,362 --> 00:25:32,197
that the three of you
would never understand.

558
00:25:33,031 --> 00:25:36,243
What? We didn't hear you
because we had in our earbuds.

559
00:25:37,327 --> 00:25:41,122
I was just saying that Paxton and I
are taking things slow, and we're good.

560
00:25:42,499 --> 00:25:43,625
Okay.

561
00:25:44,167 --> 00:25:47,504
It's just that you said some
pretty mean stuff about us before, so…

562
00:25:47,587 --> 00:25:49,839
-I don't think so. Doesn't sound like us.
-Mm-mm.

563
00:25:49,923 --> 00:25:51,049
No, you definitely did.

564
00:25:51,132 --> 00:25:52,801
She said we're not mean.

565
00:25:52,884 --> 00:25:55,220
And you labeling us that
makes you a bully.

566
00:25:55,303 --> 00:25:57,889
The prettiest girls at school
are always the ones people bully.

567
00:25:57,973 --> 00:25:59,349
[Carley and Shira] Mm-hmm.

568
00:25:59,432 --> 00:26:02,185
[McEnroe] Right then
Devi learned a valuable lesson.

569
00:26:02,269 --> 00:26:04,104
She was nothing to these girls.

570
00:26:04,187 --> 00:26:07,399
So maybe what they said
should mean nothing to her.

571
00:26:08,525 --> 00:26:11,069
Thank you.
I got a lot out of this conversation.

572
00:26:11,152 --> 00:26:12,737
-Great chat.
-Bye.

573
00:26:12,821 --> 00:26:13,989
-Great stuff. Bye.
-Bye.

574
00:26:15,323 --> 00:26:19,077
So, Devi, how was your evening last night?
Was it eventful?

575
00:26:20,745 --> 00:26:23,790
It was not. I did not consummate my plans.

576
00:26:23,873 --> 00:26:26,543
What is this?
Why are you both talking weird?

577
00:26:26,626 --> 00:26:27,752
Nothing, Mom.

578
00:26:28,336 --> 00:26:30,589
-Yo! We got idli and sambar? Noice!
-Mm-hmm.

579
00:26:30,672 --> 00:26:32,257
That definitely sounds more normal.

580
00:26:32,340 --> 00:26:35,969
So, Nirmala Mami, how was
your water aerobics class this morning?

581
00:26:36,052 --> 00:26:38,638
You still floating away,
or did you find a way to anchor yourself?

582
00:26:38,722 --> 00:26:39,639
Nobody cares, Nalu.

583
00:26:39,723 --> 00:26:41,933
Kamala, did you talk to Prashant?

584
00:26:42,475 --> 00:26:43,935
Is the wedding on or not?

585
00:26:44,019 --> 00:26:47,647
Because we need to start booking flights
for family coming from India.

586
00:26:48,148 --> 00:26:51,943
I did speak to Prashant.
It was an illuminating conversation,

587
00:26:52,027 --> 00:26:55,363
and I think we came to a mutual agreement
which we are both very happy with.

588
00:26:56,489 --> 00:26:59,117
We have decided
to not move forward with our relationship.

589
00:26:59,993 --> 00:27:02,454
But I think it's going to be
a positive thing for me, because--

590
00:27:02,537 --> 00:27:06,833
Oh, you do? I'm glad to hear it,
because I'm never speaking to you again.

591
00:27:07,959 --> 00:27:11,296
Devi, you are
my only granddaughter now. Enjoy.

592
00:27:12,005 --> 00:27:13,465
[plates clinking]

593
00:27:14,299 --> 00:27:15,300
[Nalini] All right, Mami…

594
00:27:15,383 --> 00:27:17,135
[McEnroe] Okay, well,
things were looking up.

595
00:27:17,218 --> 00:27:20,388
Devi was somehow,
for the first time, the family favorite.

596
00:27:20,472 --> 00:27:23,558
She was in a healthy relationship
with her dream guy,

597
00:27:23,642 --> 00:27:25,935
and she had learned
to ignore all the haters.

598
00:27:26,978 --> 00:27:28,605
[female voice] You better watch out, Devi.

599
00:27:28,688 --> 00:27:31,316
Paxton Hall-Yoshida
is not who you think he is.

600
00:27:31,900 --> 00:27:34,986
[McEnroe] Yeah,
it's gonna be hard to ignore that.

601
00:27:35,070 --> 00:27:37,405
♪ Yeah, I hear wedding bells ♪

602
00:27:41,743 --> 00:27:43,370
♪ But they're not for me ♪

603
00:27:48,500 --> 00:27:50,251
♪ They're for my best friend ♪

604
00:27:55,173 --> 00:27:57,008
♪ And your best friend ♪

605
00:28:01,096 --> 00:28:03,765
♪ Yeah, I hear wedding bells ♪

606
00:28:09,062 --> 00:28:11,731
♪ Yeah, I hear wedding bells ♪

607
00:28:14,317 --> 00:28:16,027
♪ But they're not for you ♪

608
00:28:25,829 --> 00:28:27,038
[music ends]
